 Here is a sample Spring code snippet using Hugging Face transformers for NLP:

```java
@SpringBootApplication
public class NlpApplication {

  public static void main(String[] args) {
    SpringApplication.run(NlpApplication.class, args);
  }

  @Bean
  public Pipeline pipeline() {
    return new Pipeline()
      .setTokenizer(new Tokenizer("bert-base-cased"))
      .setModel(new BertForSequenceClassification.Model("bert-base-cased"))
      .setFeatureExtractor(new BertFeatureExtractor("bert-base-cased")); 
  }

  @RestController
  public class NlpController {

    @Autowired
    private Pipeline pipeline;

    @PostMapping("/nlp")
    public String analyze(@RequestBody String text) {
      List<NamedEntity> entities = pipeline.process(text).getEntities();
      // analyze entities
      return "Processed text";
    }

  }

}
```

This creates a Hugging Face pipeline using a BERT model for NLP. The `Pipeline` bean is autowired into the controller and can process text through the `/nlp` endpoint. The pipeline extracts named entities which can then be analyzed further.

